<HEADLINE>
<P>
POP MUSIC CHARTS: HERE TO 'STAY'? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Lisa Loeb's "Stay," from the "Reality Bites" soundtrack, is one of the 
surprise hits of the year, topping The Times' Southern California pop singles 
chart and ranking second nationally. Such old-style folkie ballads rarely reach 
the Top 50, let alone the No. 1 spot. What's even more amazing is that Loeb is 
an unknown who's never recorded an album. In fact, she doesn't even have a 
record contract. Partly due to "Stay," the "Reality Bites" soundtrack is 
selling well--coming in at No. 17 on both the Southern California and national 
charts. TOP 10 ALBUMS 03,04,40,11 Title, Artist (Nat'l Rank) Last Week 1 The 
Lion King, soundtrack (1) 1 2 Forrest Gump, soundtrack (2) 2 3 Purple, Stone 
Temple Pilots (4) 4 4 August. . .After, Counting Crows (5) 9 5 Smash, Offspring 
(14) 7 6 The Sign, Ace of Base (3) 8 7 Voodoo Lounge, Rolling Stones (8) 5 8 
Superunknown, Soundgarden (7) 10 9 It Takes a Thief, Coolio (12) 3 10 Regulate. 
. .G-Funk Era, Warren G. (6) 11 TOP 10 SINGLES 03,04,39,11 Title, Artist 
(National Rank) Last Week 1 Stay, Lisa Loeb & Nine Stories (2) 2 2 Funkdafied, 
Da Brat (3) 3 3 Fantastic Voyage, Coolio (1) 1 4 I Swear, All-4-One (4) 4 5 
When Can I See You, Babyface (14) 16 6 Bop Gun, Ice Cube (33) 7 7 This D.J., 
Warren G. (9) 6 8 I Miss You, Aaron Hall (8) 12 9 Regulate, Warren G. and Nate 
Dogg (5) 5 10 Can You Feel. . ., Elton John (10) 8 TOP 10 HARD ROCK ALBUMS 
03,04,37,11 Title, Artist (National Rank) Last Week 1 Purple, Stone Temple 
Pilots (1) 1 2 Smash, Offspring (4) 2 3 Superunknown, Soundgarden (2) 3 4 
Candlebox, Candlebox (3) 4 5 Dookie, Green Day (5) 5 6 Get a Grip, Aerosmith 
(6) 8 7 Ill Communication, Beastie Boys (7) 6 8 Siamese. . ., Smashing Pumpkins 
(8) 9 9 The Crow, soundtrack (9) 7 10 Jar of Flies, Alice in Chains (13) 10 
Source: SoundScan Inc., for week of July 31 
</P>
