<HEADLINE>
<P>
RECORD RACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Dennis Hunt 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 ** C+C Music Factory, "Anything Goes," Columbia. A disappointing follow-up to 
producers-writers Robert Clivilles and David Cole's 1990 debut, the dance-music 
classic "Gonna Make You Sweat."There are no irresistible funk-driven tracks, 
but there are a few red-hot Latin dance tunes featuring the hip-hop trio 
Trilogy. Martha Wash shines in a limited role, but lead singer Zelma Davis is a 
bore. 
</P>
<P>
 New albums are rated on a scale of one star (poor), two stars (fair), three 
stars (good) and four stars (excellent).  
</P>
<P>
 Dennis Hunt 
</P>
