<HEADLINE>
<P>
RECORD RACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Randy Lewis 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *** Bob Woodruff, "Dreams and Saturday Nights," Asylum. The country newcomer 
(who appears at the House of Blues on Aug. 19) is a literate observer of life's 
gritty realities, and his underdog's-eye view makes him a spiritual descendant 
of Gram Parsons.If Woodruff has a fault, it's that he may have too much to say 
-- and often does. Musical textures are impressively varied, from 
Creedence-like swamp-rock to heartland rock to pure honky-tonk. New albums are 
rated on a scale of one star (poor), two stars (fair), three stars (good) and 
four stars (excellent).  
</P>
<P>
 Randy Lewis 
</P>
