<HEADLINE>
<P>
RECORD RACK: MC EIHT HITS BULL'S EYE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Dennis Hunt 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *** 1/2 MC Eiht, "We Come Strapped," Epic Street. The innovative music -- 
featuring the silky synthesizer sound of '70s R&B -- helps separate this from 
the rest of the gangsta-rap pack.So does Eiht's dramatic rapping, which adds a 
genuinely sinister quality to such songs as "Take 2 With Me." The fourth solo 
album by overlooked Eiht (a member of Compton's Most Wanted) is arguably the 
best of the year so far in the gangsta genre. 
</P>
<P>
 New albums are rated on a scale of one star (poor), two stars (fair), three 
stars (good) and four stars (excellent).  
</P>
<P>
 Dennis Hunt 
</P>
</TEXT>
