<HEADLINE>
<P>
POP EYE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 AND ONE MORE THING: The Rhino Records store -- in the pre-CD days one of the 
top spots for used albums -- has found an appropriate way to celebrate its 21st 
birthday.Each Saturday this month, the Westwood store will hold a parking lot 
sale with every item going for just 21 cents. 
</P>
<P>
 The bulk of the material being sold was acquired recently from the estate of a 
collector who had amassed about 200,000 albums covering virtually all genres of 
music. A new batch of about 40,000 will be put out for each sale day, with 
those unsold at the end of the day carted away for a fitting demise: They'll be 
melted down and recycled for new LPs and singles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
