<HEADLINE>
<P>
U.S. SHOULD EXCHANGE TIT FOR TAT IN TRADING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gene Pomerantz is on target with his "Buy American" letter ("U.S. Citizens 
Need a 'Buy American' Push," July 31).Someone high up ought to appeal to all 
Americans to buy our own products and put our people back to work. 
</P>
<P>
 And I'd like to add a suggestion to his: Let's make it as difficult for the 
Japanese and others to place their automobiles in our market as they've made it 
for American companies to crack their markets. 
</P>
<P>
 Are you listening, Mickey Kantor? 
</P>
<P>
 JERRY COWLE, Pacific Palisades 
</P>
