<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS, TIPS & BARGAINS; NEW SERVICE ON MGM GRAND AIR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 MGM Grand Air, which has focused mainly on first-class charter service, will 
begin scheduled commercial service between New York, Los Angeles and Las Vegas 
on Sept. 8. 
</P>
<P>
 Company officials said the idea is to link America's two largest cities with 
Las Vegas, the nation's fastest growing market. 
</P>
<P>
 There will be two round-trip flights between LAX and JFK daily, except 
Saturdays and on Thursday and Sunday, one flight that makes a loop from LAX to 
Las Vegas to New York and back. 
</P>
<P>
 MGM Grand Air will specialize in what it calls "Grand Class" commercial 
service -- featuring fine food, sleeping accommodations, stand-up bars and an 
array of business services -- with prices to match. The one-way fare to New 
York is $1,423; to Las Vegas, $182. 
</P>
