<HEADLINE>
<P>
CD SPOTLIGHT; SINGING A SOULFUL 'ADIOS' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Robert Hilburn 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *** 1/2; VARIOUS ARTISTS; "Adios Amigo: A Tribute to Arthur Alexander", Razor 
& Tie  
</P>
<P>
 In the flood of tribute compilations, this is a standout -- the first 
indication being the distinguished artists who have contributed versions of 
songs by Arthur Alexander. He's the late R&B singer-songwriter best known for 
his "Anna" (recorded by the Beatles) and "You Better Move On" (the Rolling 
Stones).Among those on board: Frank Black, Elvis Costello, Chuck Jackson, Mark 
Knopfler (on guitar), Graham Parker, Robert Plant and John Prine. 
</P>
<P>
 But the album's chief revelation is the emotional purity of Alexander's songs, 
mostly soulful ballads with a country tinge and heart-stirring sentimentality. 
A gem. 
</P>
<P>
 New albums are rated on a scale of one star (poor), two stars (fair), three 
stars (good) and four stars (excellent).  
</P>
<P>
 Robert Hilburn 
</P>
</TEXT>
