<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEEDLESS ROADBLOCKS WON'T SOLVE BUILDING ISSUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * If one were to take the Silvers' July 31 article criticizing the speeding up 
of the city development permits seriously, one would think that they had the 
answer to the Valley's building problems. 
</P>
<P>
 The homeowners association of which they are members protested the 
construction of the building at the southeast corner of Ventura Boulevard and 
Woodman Avenue.The building permit was delayed. The owner of the property went 
into bankruptcy fighting City Hall for a permit to build, and the boarded-up 
stores have been in such disrepair that they resemble the worst blight in any 
commercial area of Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 The "do-gooder" homeowners associations, by throwing unnecessary road blocks 
in front of Ventura Boulevard construction, have caused builders such expense 
that they either bankrupted the builder or cause the costs to go up so much 
that the project is not economically sound. 
</P>
<P>
 DANIEL POSTAR 
</P>
<P>
 Sherman Oaks 
</P>
</TEXT>
