<P>
BASKETBALL / WORLD CHAMPIONSHIPS; KOMAZEC LEADS CROATIAN VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Arijan Komazec, who didn't play the first 13 minutes, scored 17 of his 25 
points in the second half, leading a rally that carried Croatia to an 83-69 
victory over Australia in the World Championship of Basketball on Saturday at 
Toronto. 
</P>
<P>
 Croatia won its third in a row to finish in first place in Pool B. Australia 
(2-1) also has a berth in the championship bracket. 
</P>
<P>
 Australia, which got 19 points from former Seton Hall star Andrew Gaze and 16 
from Mark Bradtke, led by as many as six points in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
 Russia 73, Canada 66 -- Russia outscored Canada, 10-2, in the final 1:35 to 
win Pool C in a game at Hamilton. The teams were even throughout the second 
half until Russia (3-0) pulled away. 
</P>
<P>
 Cuba 92, South Korea 79 -- Angel Caballero scored 30 points on 11-for-12 
shooting in a Pool B game at Toronto. Caballero made all four of his 
three-point shots. 
</P>
<P>
 Argentina 67, Angola 59 -- Marcelo Nicola had 25 points and 11 rebounds at 
Hamilton to lead Argentina to third place in Pool C. Nicola's three-point play 
with nine minutes left brought Argentina (1-2) into a 50-50 tie. It took the 
lead for good 48 seconds later on a three-pointer by Juan Espil. 
</P>
