<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOODLAND HILLS TIGERS ADVANCE TO FINAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Woodland Hills Tigers defeated the Norwalk Rebels, 7-4, at Downey High on 
Saturday to advance to the final of the Stan Musial regional tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 The Tigers (34-9), composed of college and semipro players, would advance to 
the state tournament with a victory today. 
</P>
<P>
 Mike Jenkins (6-0), formerly of Simi Valley High, went six innings, allowing 
three hits and two earned runs. 
</P>
<P>
 The Tigers trailed, 3-0, before scoring six runs in the third inning. Two-run 
doubles by Brent Christenson, a Brigham Young player formerly of Thousand Oaks 
High, and Paul Blair Jr. highlighted the inning. 
</P>
