GARDENER'S CHECKLIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By For dedicated gardeners, here are suggestions from the California Assn. of 
Nurserymen on what to do in the garden this week: 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Harvest summer vegetables frequently to extend production. 
</P>
<P>
 * Cut to 12 inches from soil level all hydrangeas stalks that bloomed this 
year. 
</P>
<P>
 * Feed citrus and avocados. 
</P>
<P>
 * Pinch off fuchsia seed pods to extend production. 
</P>
<P>
 * Plant perennials during the next six weeks for bloom next spring and for 
years to come. 
</P>
